<div class="comment"><div class="commtext c00">Any speed up that is 2x is definitely worth fixing. Especially since someone has already figured out the issue and performance testing [1] shows that llamacpp* is lagging behind vLLM by 2x. This is a positive for all running LLMs locally using llamacpp.<p>Even if llamacpp isnt used for batch inference now, this can allow those to finally run llamacpp for batching and on any hardware since vLLM supports only select hardware. Maybe finally we can stop all this gpu api software fragmentation and cuda moat as llamacpp benchmarks have shown Vulkan to be as or more performant than cuda or sycl.<p>[1] <a href="https:&#x2F;&#x2F;miro.medium.com&#x2F;v2&#x2F;resize:fit:1400&#x2F;format:webp&#x2F;1*labdDV6bkGlbL5OGZXJkEA.png" rel="nofollow">https:&#x2F;&#x2F;miro.medium.com&#x2F;v2&#x2F;resize:fit:1400&#x2F;format:webp&#x2F;1*lab...</a></div><div class="reply"><p><font size="1"><u><a href="reply?id=44368471&amp;goto=item%3Fid%3D44365320%2344368471" rel="nofollow">reply</a></u></font></div></div></td></tr>
